ActTerritorial Lands Act
PrecisORDER RESPECTING THE WITHDRAWAL FROM DISPOSAL OF CERTAIN LANDS IN THE NORTHWEST TERRITORIES (EAST ARM OF GREAT SLAVE LAKE, N.W.T.) - which provides the withdrawal from disposal the surface and subsurface rights of certain lands (approximately 26,350 square kilometres), in order to facilitate the establishment of a national park, East Arm of Great Slave Lake, in the Northwest Territories.
